summary: This document is a calendar entry for a scheduled phone call with Jeffrey Epstein on March 1, 2019, organized by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS). It indicates official contact between federal prosecutors and Epstein after his 2019 arrest.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: The scheduled call is with him, indicating direct contact with federal prosecutors from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York in 2019.

events.title: Scheduled Call with Jeffrey Epstein
events.description: A 30-minute phone call was scheduled between the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) and Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: The U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) had a scheduled phone call with Jeffrey Epstein on March 1, 2019.
The call was scheduled for 30 minutes, from 18:30 to 19:00 UTC.
This document shows official contact between federal prosecutors and Epstein after his July 2019 arrest, placing the call approximately four months before his death in August 2019.
